Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.68,0:00:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut the world is even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.02,0:00:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case has the scent of honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.02,0:00:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a stinger behind the sweetness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.61,0:00:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.72,0:00:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.07,0:01:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Honey Cocktail Murder Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.64,0:02:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.97,0:02:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, isn't President Yamazaki\Nthe head of Yamazaki Development,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.14,0:02:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the company you did a bodyguard\Njob for during that blackmail case?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you invited to today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.15,0:02:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She says she has a favor to ask\Nof the nationally famous Mori Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.59,0:02:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome! Mori-{\i1}sama{\i0}, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.59,0:02:46.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Aihara Shingo (53) Caretaker
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.26,0:02:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The president is expecting you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.36,0:02:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}sama{\i0} is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.07,0:02:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.15,0:02:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.74,0:03:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.11,0:03:04.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yamazaki Hiromi (50)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.24,0:03:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to call you all the way
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.66,0:03:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,into the mountains like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.87,0:03:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see you're as beautiful as ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're a flatterer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.75,0:03:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce you. This is the\NMayor of Iwami, Hachimaki-{\i1}sama{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.13,0:03:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Hachimaki Hachibe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.13,0:03:24.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachimaki Hachibe (62) Mayor of Iwami City
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.67,0:03:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to meet the distinguished\NMori Kogoro-{\i1}san {\i0}like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.39,0:03:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:31.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakamura Eri (32) Pres. Yamazaki's Secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Nakamura, her secretary. It's nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.39,0:03:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pleasure's all mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Aihara, the caretaker here.\NIf you need anything, just let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.53,0:03:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.20,0:03:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now if you'll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this model of?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.04,0:03:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know not to touch,\NConan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.46,0:03:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.25,0:04:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}, this is the\NIwami Spa Resort we're planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.34,0:04:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from the hot springs,\Nit'll have a golf range, a tennis club,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an arcade, and many other facilities!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.31,0:04:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our city's population is dwindling,\Nso I've teamed up with
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.27,0:04:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,President Yamazaki to build a\Nspa resort to give it a shot in the arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.57,0:04:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow is the ground-breaking ceremony!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.53,0:04:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we'd like you to\Nplay a part in the advertising,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.78,0:04:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by appearing in magazines and\Ntelevision commercials as a model.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.58,0:04:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Model in your commercials?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.33,0:04:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.13,0:04:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting too excited...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.26,0:04:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's set aside the business talk for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.68,0:04:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aihara... prepare the early celebration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.47,0:04:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'll bring it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.74,0:05:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An afternoon with a rare feast\Nand sake... There's nothing better!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.32,0:05:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wild boar stew and fresh Iwami vegetables!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.49,0:05:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They all share the\Nsimple flavors of this region!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.33,0:05:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, local cuisine will be\None of the resort's attractions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.38,0:05:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming from your upstairs office.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! Mayor! Why don't\Nyou let Mori-{\i1}san {\i0}try the specialties?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that? Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.15,0:05:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Aihara-{\i1}kun{\i0}!\NBring you-know-what out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.20,0:05:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.58,0:05:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are "the specialties"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.67,0:06:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll just have to wait and see!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.47,0:06:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aihara-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.59,0:06:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uhh, please send over\None case of beer and juice!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking you-know-what.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.23,0:06:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.69,0:06:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now these are the pride of our town!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Newt and wasp sake!\NThey're incredibly revitalizing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.58,0:06:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, drink up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.09,0:06:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I've had too much to drink.\NI need some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.77,0:06:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.73,0:07:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was such nice weather earlier, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.98,0:07:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mountain weather does change quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.36,0:07:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like they say, a woman's\Nheart is as fickle as autumn weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.17,0:07:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That was President Yamazaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.21,0:07:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police and a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.77,0:07:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A balloon...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An insecticide spray?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.74,0:08:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.22,0:08:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.10,0:08:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, are you the famous\Ndetective, Mori Kogoro-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.64,0:08:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.85,0:08:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Suzuki, a resident police officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.57,0:08:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Dr. Sakurai,\Nwho runs a clinic in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I leave the rest to you.\NI'm going to have a look at her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This door locks automatically, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.04,0:08:47.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.29,0:08:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}! I have a spare key!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It smells like insecticide!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.39,0:09:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears it was\Nlocked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.49,0:09:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears she broke the\Nwindow to get onto the veranda,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.37,0:09:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then she fell over when\Nthe rail she was leaning on broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.79,0:09:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.21,0:09:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.33,0:09:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Sakurai says she died\Nof head injuries when she fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.68,0:09:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This office has an automatic lock,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.55,0:09:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and all upstairs windows\Nwere locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be impossible to sneak\Npast us on the first floor to go upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And sneaking in via the\Nchimney would also be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.19,0:09:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was a completely locked room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.54,0:10:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is--!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.29,0:10:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, officer! This is a bee, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.71,0:10:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a yellowjacket wasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.30,0:10:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Dr. Sakurai\Ndid find sting marks on her head.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sting marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.93,0:10:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are wasps common in this area?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.26,0:10:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.72,0:10:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, wasn't she\Nafraid of wasps, Nakamura-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.06,0:10:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's from here, and she'd had\Na traumatic childhood experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.15,0:10:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some wasps stung her in the sixth grade,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.07,0:10:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Aihara-{\i1}san {\i0}saved\Nher on the verge of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.16,0:10:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she hired him\Nto take care of the mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.66,0:10:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because she owed him her life...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.34,0:10:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:11:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always had bug spray on hand\Nto keep wasps from coming inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.09,0:11:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There've been many wasp-related\Nincidents so far this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.85,0:11:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured out the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.44,0:11:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the wasps that killed her,\Nno question about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.36,0:11:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen... President Yamazaki\Nmust've been attacked
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by wasps that entered\Nthrough that fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She tried using the nearby bug spray,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but in her panic, she went\Nthrough the window and onto the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.54,0:11:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, as luck would have it,\Nthe handrail broke and she fell over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.71,0:11:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.22,0:11:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did she escape\Nthrough the window and not the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.27,0:11:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When people panic, they lose\Nthe ability to make good judgments.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.20,0:12:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this sticky stuff?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is--!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.97,0:12:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This might not have been an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.64,0:12:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible it was a murder\Nplotted by one of these people!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.12,0:12:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Protective clothing for handling wasps!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.84,0:13:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These two bottles were used recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.09,0:13:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ether and sulfuric acid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.85,0:13:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Helium? Why is this here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.35,0:13:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.03,0:13:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, it went downstream!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.98,0:13:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fishing line and a ripped plastic bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this black dirt!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.53,0:14:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rain cap that should\Nbe on this chimney is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.83,0:14:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some of the soot inside it\Nhas been rubbed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.80,0:14:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scotch tape?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.93,0:14:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hole in the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.73,0:14:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Now I see how the trick worked!\NThat person is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd that runt disappear to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.20,0:14:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.78,0:14:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You always worry us\Nwhen you suddenly disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.75,0:15:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit scampering around! Come with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.75,0:15:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. Have a nap\Nand leave the rest to me, old guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the--?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.39,0:15:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! What was that sound?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.73,0:15:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.81,0:15:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.94,0:15:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it out, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.23,0:15:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.94,0:15:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't an accident?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.70,0:15:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say that now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.66,0:15:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To catch the killer off guard.\NI wanted time to gather proof, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.41,0:15:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person responsible\Nmurdered President Yamazaki
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and made it look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.79,0:15:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What proof do you have to--?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.67,0:15:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a look at the inside doorknob.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:15:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?\NNothing seems out of the ordinary...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.39,0:15:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Underneath the connecting part.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.86,0:16:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is--!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.77,0:16:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.82,0:16:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If wasps attacked you inside,\Nyou would normally run out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.99,0:16:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there were a bunch of\Nwasps on the honey-covered doorknob,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.79,0:16:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so President Yamazaki ran in\Nthe opposite direction, to the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rail on the veranda was quite corroded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.96,0:16:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It had been corroded in\Nadvance using sulfuric acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what about the wasps?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.97,0:16:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... the wasps were planned too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.47,0:16:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a look at the ceiling behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.19,0:16:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the balloon that--?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.40,0:16:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.57,0:16:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the balloon you and Conan\Nsaw on your way down to the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It got stuck to a\Ntree branch downstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.28,0:17:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, check the plastic bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.25,0:17:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.88,0:17:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wasp!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer put wasps into\Nthe bag attached to the balloon
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and placed it in the chimney.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were probably gathered\Nafter spraying them with ether.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.72,0:17:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aihara-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.10,0:17:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found a beekeeper outfit\Nthat smelled of ether in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most everyone in this area has one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.57,0:17:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what are the\Nhelium tanks in the shed for?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.24,0:17:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We made balloons for\Nkids at the summer festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.37,0:17:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're what's left over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.55,0:17:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder. There were three tanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you didn't do\Na lot of test flights of a balloon
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a bag attached instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.51,0:17:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed to mean?\NWhat are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:18:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the caretaker here\Ncould have set all this up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.51,0:18:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! You're the killer,\NAihara-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.23,0:18:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the living room when she fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.17,0:18:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was with all of you!\NHow could I have killed her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.36,0:18:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, to temporarily keep\Nthe balloon inside the chimney,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you tied fishing line to it,\Nled it to the downstairs kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.25,0:18:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,through a small hole in the floor\Nby the fireplace, and tied it to a nail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.63,0:18:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You also stuck fishing line\Nto a piece of tape on the bag
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.67,0:18:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and led it to the kitchen as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.96,0:18:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything was then ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.93,0:18:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The phone rang, and President\NYamazaki went to the upstairs office.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.47,0:18:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, you were on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.35,0:18:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... you had called her upstairs\Noffice to get her into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.53,0:18:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After confirming that\Nshe had picked up the receiver,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.70,0:19:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you pulled a thread leading into the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.82,0:19:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tape covering a pre-made\Nrip in the bag came off
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.83,0:19:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and sent the wasps flying out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The balloon blocked the chimney's top,\Nso they flew into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.67,0:19:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The agitated wasps then\Nattacked President Yamazaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.43,0:19:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While spraying the insecticide,\Nshe headed for the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.52,0:19:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she was unable to open it.\NBecause it was crawling with wasps.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.02,0:19:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With no other choice, she ran\Naround the room, broke the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.15,0:19:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and leapt onto the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.99,0:19:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She leaned against the rail\Nand aimed the spray at the wasps,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.49,0:19:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the rail broke and she fell over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.41,0:19:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After we rushed outside,\Nyou quickly returned to the kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.46,0:19:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and undid the other thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.37,0:19:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so the balloon\Nwent flying out of the chimney.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.38,0:20:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Ran\Nand Conan happened to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But something didn't go as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.72,0:20:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The balloon was supposed to\Nfly far off into the distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the light rain and wind\Nunfortunately got it stuck in a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.15,0:20:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found the tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.65,0:20:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there is a hole in the floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.78,0:20:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't prove anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.24,0:20:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aihara-{\i1}san{\i0}. Could you\Nshow us the towel on your hip?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.49,0:20:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Towel?! Wh-What about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.71,0:20:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The doorknob must've been\Nentirely covered in honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.38,0:20:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you didn't\Nwipe it away with your towel?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.60,0:20:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is honey on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.81,0:20:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.06,0:20:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take out what's\Nin your right pants pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.61,0:21:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter? Show it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.78,0:21:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the very same thread\Nthat undid the tape on the plastic bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.74,0:21:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mayor and Conan\Nhad barged in just then,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.08,0:21:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you hastily stuffed it into your pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.67,0:21:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears you didn't have\Ntime to dispose of the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.55,0:21:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That, or you lowered your guard\Nwhen it was deemed an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.88,0:21:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making me the caretaker because\NI saved her life was nice and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.26,0:21:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I wound up like a worker\Nbee slaving away for the queen bee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.23,0:21:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she said she'd make\Nme manager of the spa resort,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.48,0:21:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I tried so hard to endure it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.82,0:21:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was a lie. A big, fat lie.\NI couldn't stand it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.45,0:21:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to ruin tomorrow's\Nground-breaking ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.41,0:21:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I had to do it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.84,0:23:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Dad! You solved the case!\NYou're a genius, as always!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.72,0:23:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly! That was a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.08,0:23:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, I'm hungry!\NPlus we didn't go to the hot springs!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.39,0:23:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's hit the\Nhot springs and get manlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.28,0:23:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping Kogoro gets to\Nshow off his mind and body!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.53,0:24:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing you\Ncan show off is how to sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.04,0:24:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.73,0:24:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The room is filled with idol posters!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.07,0:24:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two of everything,\Neven photo books and CDs!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.70,0:24:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they have their names on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.49,0:24:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This wasn't a suicide! It was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.00,0:24:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this was a sealed room!\NHow did the killer escape?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.61,0:24:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.16,0:24:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Sealed Bathroom Murder Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.32,0:24:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.48,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adhesive tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.85,0:24:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode takes place at the home of two beautiful sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.65,0:24:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Specifically, their bathroom. No peeping, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.62,0:24:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
